# Skippy browser extension

## Layout

- `plugin/` is the loadable extension root — every file referenced in `manifest.json` must live under it.
- Do not add build tooling or repo docs inside `plugin/` unless the extension needs them at runtime.

## Cross-browser APIs

Use the WebExtension pattern everywhere:

```javascript
const storage = (typeof browser !== "undefined") ? browser.storage.sync : chrome.storage.sync;
```

Prefer `browser.*` promise APIs; fall back to `chrome.*` for Chromium.

## Manifest changes

- Bump `version` in `manifest.json` for any user-facing release.
- New host permissions or content-script `matches` patterns require updating `permissions` / `content_scripts` and documenting in README.
- Content scripts only run on `https://www.youtube.com/watch*` — broaden matches deliberately (performance + review implications).

## Content script (`processor.js`)

- Polls storage for the server base URL; appends `/api/v2/timestamps` — never hardcode full API URLs in popup placeholder text.
- Detects SPA navigation via History API hooks + URL polling — preserve this when refactoring video-change detection.
- Skip check runs on a 5s interval; timestamp fetch re-triggers when the stored server URL changes.

## Popup (`popup.js` / `popup.html`)

- Server URL is the **base origin** only (e.g. `https://api.example.com`), saved to `storage.sync` under key `server`.
- Register event listeners once (inside `DOMContentLoaded`).

## Testing checklist

1. Reload unpacked extension after any `plugin/` change.
2. Refresh open YouTube tabs (content scripts do not hot-reload).
3. Set server URL in popup → confirm `storage.sync` persists across browser restart.
4. Open a watch URL → verify GET to `/api/v2/timestamps?link=...` in Network tab.
5. With known timestamps, confirm playback jumps past `start_time`–`end_time` ranges.
6. Navigate to another video without full page reload → confirm new timestamps are fetched.

## Scope discipline

- Minimal diffs; no frameworks or bundlers unless the project outgrows vanilla JS.
- Keep console prefix `[YouTube Tracker]` consistent unless renaming project-wide.
